headline: Zillow, Other Online Home Listings Stocks Drop. Google is Entering the Fray.
summary: The turf war over real estate listings could get a big new entrant.  Stocks for companies with home for-sale listing websites fell sharply on Monday on news that  Alphabet  Google is testing homes for-sale ads at the top of search results.  Shares of  Zillow  were down 10.3%, to $67, on Monday morning.

headline: Stock Market Today: Dow Edges Up As Tesla Jumps Near Buy Point, Apple Lags (Live Coverage)
